<dl id="n37009l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n37" href="#n37009l">N37 (VI.B.28A)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n37all.htm#n37009l"> 9(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 215 sucker</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<font size="-1">SUNDRIES AND AN AUTOBIOGRAPHY</font>]</font>: The American people were looking for a philosophy of Success, and Barnum combined for them &ldquo;There&apos;s a <mark>sucker</mark> born every minute,&rdquo; with &ldquo;Honesty is the Best Policy.&rdquo; These truths &hellip; formed the metaphysics of business, whose Aristotle was Barnum. <small> M.R. Werner, <a name="MRWP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MRWP"><cite title="source">P.T. Barnum</cite></a> (1923) 215</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
